      <body>
         <p><opener>
         <dateline><date when="1915-03-23">March 23, 1915</date></dateline>
         <salute>My dear <persName key="margaret_anderson">Miss Anderson</persName>:</salute></opener>
         I am enclosing an advertisement from <title key=”egoist” level="j">“The Egoist”</title> which <persName key="harriet_weaver">Miss Weaver</persName> asked me to send on to you. She said it was their regular advertisement and I need say nothing with it, that you would understand. By the way, I suppose it is all right for me to put that article on the Poetry Bookshop in your <date when="2015-05">May</date> number, <foreign xml:lang="fr">n’est-ce pas</foreign>? Also, can I criticize <persName key="john_fletcher">Fletcher</persName>’s new book, <title key="irradiations" level="m">“Radiations”</title>, for you for the <date when="2015-05">June</date> number, I guess, and who are you going to have do our <title key="" level="m">“Imagist Anthology”</title>? Do have a kindly-disposed and understanding person.
         <closer>Sincerely yours,</closer></p>
      </body>
   </text>
